# Trivy allowlist — vulnerability triage
#
# Read automatically by the `trivy-fs` CI job (severity HIGH,CRITICAL,
# ignore-unfixed). This file is the auditable escape hatch for a CVE that is
# confirmed but cannot be acted on right now, so a single unfixable advisory
# does not block every PR.
#
# Policy:
#   1. FIX FIRST. Bump the dependency (go.mod / package.json) before suppressing.
#      ignore-unfixed:true already skips advisories with no upstream fix.
#   2. Only add an entry for a HIGH/CRITICAL with a fix that we cannot take yet
#      (breaking bump, transitive pin pending, not reachable in our usage).
#   3. Every entry MUST carry: the reason, who triaged it, the date, and a
#      tracking issue. Re-review on each dependency bump and on a quarterly pass.
#   4. Prefer scoping with an expiry: an entry with no removal plan rots into a
#      silent blind spot.
#
# Format (one ID per line, `#` comments allowed):
#   CVE-2025-XXXXX  # reason; <owner> <YYYY-MM-DD>; tracking: <issue-url>
#
# --- Active suppressions ---
# (none — keep this list empty; the gate is clean)
